title: In pageant-crazy Venezuela, men compete for Miss Gay crown

In pageant-crazy Venezuela, men compete for Miss Gay crown In this Oct. 18, 2015 photo, Argenis Gonzalez wears the Miss Gay Venezuela crown after winning the beauty pageant in Caracas, Venezuela. “It’s a great achievement to get to be the face of what is such a large community in Latin America, and even bigger in our country,” said Gonzalez, a 24-year-old social media coordinator. “And to have so many straight people cheering us on makes me feel really privileged.” When not dressed as a woman, Gonzalez goes by the first name Manuel. (AP Photo/Ariana Cubillos) Most Read
